.SH NAME
devm_hwspin_lock_request_specific \- request for a specific hwspinlock for a managed device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct hwspinlock *" devm_hwspin_lock_request_specific
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "unsigned int id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the device to request the specific hwspinlock
.IP "id" 12
index of the specific hwspinlock that is requested
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function should be called by users of the hwspinlock module,
in order to assign them a specific hwspinlock.
Usually early board code will be calling this function in order to
reserve specific hwspinlock ids for predefined purposes.

Should be called from a process context (might sleep)

Returns the address of the assigned hwspinlock, or NULL on error
